      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate VAD operating envelope (flow rates 3–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2400–3600 RPM) with documented fluid temperature, viscosity, and hematocrit matching COU specifications. At least 4 of 5 operating points must be physically tested.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions were set to match three of five target operating points. Fluid properties were controlled and documented. Achieved level 2 because two operating points were extrapolated rather than directly tested, reducing confidence in boundary condition fidelity."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Predicted hemolysis index values were compared against experimental measurements. Agreement was within 30% for three operating points but exceeded 50% error for two points. Required level 4 was set as appropriate for MRL 5; achieved level 2 indicates insufficient quantitative agreement for absolute prediction claims."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly mapped to clinical hemolysis thresholds specified in the device submission. The mapping must be documented with uncertainty bounds derived from the Monte Carlo UQ study.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) was selected as the primary QoI and mapped to the clinical threshold. Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds were computed. Achieved level 3 because the mapping documentation lacked a formal sensitivity analysis linking NIH uncertainty to clinical decision uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry rather than the actual VAD device geometry. Geometric similarity was argued but not quantified. Required level 4 was noted as necessary for MRL 5; achieved level 2 reflects the significant geometric gap between the validation platform and the COU device."
