      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and boundary condition inputs must be sourced from traceable measurements or published standards. Input uncertainty distributions must be defined for Monte Carlo propagation. At least 500 Monte Carlo samples must be used to characterize output uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Input parameters including blood viscosity, density, and inlet velocity profiles were sourced from published literature. Monte Carlo sampling with 1000 draws was performed. Achieved level 2 because several secondary inputs (e.g., erythrocyte mechanical properties) lacked traceable experimental sources and were assigned nominal literature values without uncertainty characterization."
    },
